WEBVTT

0
00:00:03.250 --> 00:00:04.750
So we have covered the history,

1
00:00:04.949 --> 00:00:06.230
the wreck architecture,

2
00:00:06.280 --> 00:00:08.109
and the cooling specifications.

3
00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:11.760
Now it's time to map out your actual deployment journey.

4
00:00:12.619 --> 00:00:15.859
And that journey starts with a vigorous facility assessment.

5
00:00:16.840 --> 00:00:18.889
Before you buy a single piece of hardware,

6
00:00:19.010 --> 00:00:20.649
you must evaluate your site

7
00:00:20.850 --> 00:00:23.290
against some critical readiness factors.

8
00:00:23.639 --> 00:00:24.319
In general,

9
00:00:24.569 --> 00:00:26.309
there are 3 areas

10
00:00:26.450 --> 00:00:28.319
that are the focus of this assessment.

11
00:00:28.690 --> 00:00:29.049
First,

12
00:00:29.290 --> 00:00:30.209
power density.

13
00:00:30.420 --> 00:00:33.909
Can your facility support the required power density?

14
00:00:34.369 --> 00:00:34.810
Second,

15
00:00:35.049 --> 00:00:36.319
thermal capacity.

16
00:00:36.529 --> 00:00:39.889
Are you prepared to root liquid cooling manifolds?

17
00:00:40.180 --> 00:00:40.750
And third,

18
00:00:40.970 --> 00:00:42.049
physical weight.

19
00:00:42.400 --> 00:00:45.930
Fully populated RV3 regs are incredibly heavy.

20
00:00:46.319 --> 00:00:51.349
So your structural floors must be able to support this massive load in a safe way.

21
00:00:52.169 --> 00:00:52.490
Now,

22
00:00:52.689 --> 00:00:54.279
once your facility is cleared,

23
00:00:54.450 --> 00:00:56.889
your next stop is the OCP marketplace.

24
00:00:57.959 --> 00:01:01.709
This is your central hub for procuring verified hardware.

25
00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:05.650
You'll want to look exclusively for the OCP accepted badge.

26
00:01:05.959 --> 00:01:09.480
These are officially recognized products that strictly adhere

27
00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:11.779
to the designs published in our database.

28
00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:13.290
And remember,

29
00:01:13.629 --> 00:01:17.050
OCP accepted gear guarantees proven efficiency,

30
00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:21.790
whether you're building a new data center or replacing legacy 19-inch racks.

31
00:01:23.190 --> 00:01:26.440
But what if your current facility fails the assessment?

32
00:01:27.819 --> 00:01:29.650
If your forces can't handle the weight,

33
00:01:29.870 --> 00:01:31.809
or you lack the cooling infrastructure.

34
00:01:32.569 --> 00:01:34.650
You don't have to abandon the transition.

35
00:01:35.580 --> 00:01:40.360
You can migrate your operations to an OCP ready co-location facilities.

36
00:01:41.599 --> 00:01:44.330
These are heavily audited third party sites

37
00:01:44.449 --> 00:01:48.410
that are purpose built specifically to house OCP hardware.

38
00:01:49.660 --> 00:01:50.519
Transitioning

39
00:01:50.819 --> 00:01:53.559
to open infrastructure is a massive undertaking,

40
00:01:54.139 --> 00:01:55.620
but you don't have to do it alone.

41
00:01:56.879 --> 00:02:01.120
You are now part of the community and you have access to a rich ecosystem.

42
00:02:02.589 --> 00:02:06.830
The marketplace is filled with certified OCP solution providers.

43
00:02:08.358 --> 00:02:11.988
These are professional services companies and system integrators

44
00:02:11.998 --> 00:02:15.139
that are specifically trained to assess your readiness,

45
00:02:15.438 --> 00:02:16.789
design your architecture,

46
00:02:16.998 --> 00:02:19.059
and physically deploy the hardware

47
00:02:19.199 --> 00:02:20.158
on your behalf.

48
00:02:21.350 --> 00:02:24.300
The community has already done the heavy engineering for you.

49
00:02:25.220 --> 00:02:28.160
Your next step is to see it through for yourself.

50
00:02:29.389 --> 00:02:34.089
Browse the digital OCP marketplace to find your hardware and solution providers

51
00:02:34.429 --> 00:02:34.929
or

52
00:02:35.149 --> 00:02:36.089
book a visit

53
00:02:36.229 --> 00:02:38.809
to a physical OCP experience center

54
00:02:39.029 --> 00:02:40.929
to see this technology running in person.

55
00:02:42.389 --> 00:02:43.119
Welcome

56
00:02:43.309 --> 00:02:45.589
to the open compute ecosystem.